STL Algorithm1. Non-modifying sequence operations1. adjacent_find​ 用于查找相邻元素满足特定条件的第一个位置。它返回一个指向该位置的迭代器。如果没有找到相邻的满足条件的元素，则返回容器的末尾迭代器。 函数原型 12345template &lt;class ForwardIt&gt;ForwardIt adjacent_find(ForwardIt first, ForwardIt last);template &lt;class ForwardIt, class BinaryPredicate&gt;ForwardIt adjacent_find(ForwardIt first, ForwardIt last, BinaryPredicate p); 默认行为 如果没有提供自定义的二元谓词，std::adjacent_find会使用相等比较（==）判断相邻元素。 示例1： 12345678910111213141516171819#include &lt;iostream&gt;#include &lt;vector&gt;#include &lt;algorithm&gt;int main() &#123; std::vector&lt;int&gt; vec = &#123;1, 2, 3, 3, 5, 6&#125;; auto it = std::adjacent_find(vec.begin(), vec.end()); if (it != vec.end()) &#123; std::cout &lt;&lt; &quot;First adjacent equal elements found at index: &quot; &lt;&lt; std::distance(vec.begin(), it) &lt;&lt; &quot; with value: &quot; &lt;&lt; *it &lt;&lt; &#x27;
&#x27;; &#125; else &#123; std::cout &lt;&lt; &quot;No adjacent equal elements found.
&quot;; &#125; return 0;&#125; 示例2： 1234567891011121314151617181920212223#include &lt;iostream&gt;#include &lt;vector&gt;#include &lt;algorithm&gt;bool CustomPredicate(int a, int b) &#123; return (b - a == 2);&#125;int main() &#123; std::vector&lt;int&gt; vec = &#123;1, 3, 5, 6, 8&#125;; auto it = std::adjacent_find(vec.begin(), vec.end(), CustomPredicate); if (it != vec.end()) &#123; std::cout &lt;&lt; &quot;Adjacent elements satisfying custom condition found at index: &quot; &lt;&lt; std::distance(vec.begin(), it) &lt;&lt; &quot; with values: &quot; &lt;&lt; *it &lt;&lt; &quot; and &quot; &lt;&lt; *(it + 1) &lt;&lt; &#x27;
&#x27;; &#125; else &#123; std::cout &lt;&lt; &quot;No adjacent elements satisfying custom condition found.
&quot;; &#125; return 0;&#125; 2. reduce​ std::reduce是一个标准库算法，用于在指定范围内对元素进行归约操作。它在C++17中引入，属于&lt;numeric&gt;头文件的一部分。 基本语法 123456789101112131415161718192021222324252627#include &lt;numeric&gt;(1)template &lt;class InputIt&gt;typename std::iterator_traits&lt;InputIt&gt;::value_type reduce(InputIt first, InputIt last );(2)template &lt;class ExecutionPolicy, class ForwardIt&gt;typename std::iterator_traits&lt;ForwardIt&gt;::value_type reduce(ExecutionPolicy&amp;&amp; policy, ForwardIt first, ForwardIt last);(3)template &lt;class InputIt, class T&gt;T reduce(InputIt first, InputIt last, T init);(4)template &lt;class ExecutionPolicy, class ForwardIt, class T&gt;T reduce(ExecutionPolicy&amp;&amp; policy, ForwardIt first, ForwardIt last, T init);(5)template &lt;class InputIt, class T, class BinaryOp&gt;T reduce(InputIt first, InputIt last, T init, BinaryOp op);(6)template &lt;class ExecutionPolicy, class ForwardIt, class T, class BinaryOp&gt;T reduce(ExecutionPolicy&amp;&amp; policy, ForwardIt first, ForwardIt last, T init, BinaryOp op); 主要功能 对范围[first, last)的所有元素应用二元操作符binary_op，将结果累加到init上。 支持并行执行（需要执行策略）。 与std::accumulate类似，但有以下不同点： std::reduce支持并行化； std::reduce的操作顺序不固定（无序归约），需要操作满足交换律和结合律。

C++ FQA1. swap​ It turns out that we can achieve this behavior very easily, because the STL’s std::swap is deliberately written as the least-constrained kind of template possible, meaning that it ranks lowest in the overload resolution scheme. Any viable candidate found via ADL ought to rank higher than std::swap. So in real life, we just need to make sure that name lookup will always consider std::swap a candidate in addition to the ADL candidate(s) (if any). We write this: 12345template &lt;typename T&gt;void test(T&amp; t) &#123; using std::swap; // make it a candidate swap(t, t);&#125; And here we finally have the “two-step“. Step 1: using std::swap; Step 2: Unqualified call to swap(t, t). 总结： using std::swap可以将std命名空间下的swap作为candidate。如果没有customized swap，可以使用std::swap。类似的用法还有begin和end。 参考 https://quuxplusone.github.io/blog/2020/07/11/the-std-swap-two-step/ https://quuxplusone.github.io/blog/2022/04/30/poison-pill-redux/ https://eel.is/c++draft/basic.lookup.argdep#1 Name lookup 2. Type Erasure​ Type erasure based on templates is a pretty sophisticated technique. It allows you to bridge dynamic polymorphism (object orientation) with static polymorphism (templates). 1234567891011121314151617181920212223242526272829303132333435363738394041424344454647484950515253545556575859// typeErasure.cpp#include &lt;iostream&gt;#include &lt;memory&gt;#include &lt;string&gt;#include &lt;vector&gt;class Object &#123; // (2) public: template &lt;typename T&gt; // (3) Object(T&amp;&amp; obj) : object(std::make_shared&lt;Model&lt;T&gt;&gt;(std::forward&lt;T&gt;(obj))) &#123;&#125; std::string getName() const &#123; // (4) return object-&gt;getName(); &#125; struct Concept &#123; // (5) virtual ~Concept() &#123;&#125; virtual std::string getName() const = 0; &#125;; template &lt;typename T&gt; // (6) struct Model : Concept &#123; Model(const T&amp; t) : object(t) &#123;&#125; std::string getName() const override &#123; return object.getName(); &#125; private: T object; &#125;; std::shared_ptr&lt;const Concept&gt; object;&#125;;void printName(std::vector&lt;Object&gt; vec) &#123; // (7) for (auto v : vec) std::cout &lt;&lt; v.getName() &lt;&lt; &#x27;
&#x27;;&#125;struct Bar &#123; std::string getName() const &#123; // (8) return &quot;Bar&quot;; &#125;&#125;;struct Foo &#123; std::string getName() const &#123; // (8) return &quot;Foo&quot;; &#125;&#125;;int main() &#123; std::cout &lt;&lt; &#x27;
&#x27;; // 不需要自己管理指针 // 同时还支持dynamic polymorphism std::vector&lt;Object&gt; vec&#123;Object(Foo()), Object(Bar())&#125;; // (1) printName(vec); std::cout &lt;&lt; &#x27;
&#x27;;&#125; 参考 https://www.modernescpp.com/index.php/type-erasure https://davekilian.com/cpp-type-erasure.html https://quuxplusone.github.io/blog/2022/04/30/poison-pill-redux/ 3. 智能指针Implementation notes In a typical implementation, shared_ptr holds only two pointers: the stored pointer (one returned by get()); a pointer to control block. The control block is a dynamically-allocated object that holds: either a pointer to the managed object or the managed object itself; the deleter (type-erased); the allocator (type-erased); the number of shared_ptrs that own the managed object; the number of weak_ptrs that refer to the managed object. 参考 https://www.justsoftwaresolutions.co.uk/cplusplus/shared-ptr-secret-constructor.html https://www.codesynthesis.com/~boris/blog/2012/04/25/shared-ptr-aliasing-constructor/ 4. Binding to overloaded member functions参考 https://www.anteru.net/blog/2007/c-tricks-4-binding-to-overloaded-member-functions/ 5. Identity参考 https://www.cnblogs.com/happenlee/p/14721602.html 6. Propagating ‘typedef’ from based to derived class for ‘template’参考 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1643035/propagating-typedef-from-based-to-derived-class-for-template 7. I’m trying to print a Chinese character using the types wchar_t, char16_t and char32_t, to no avail参考 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/31571430/im-trying-to-print-a-chinese-character-using-the-types-wchar-t-char16-t-and-ch 8. 二进制文件读写参考 https://www.eecs.umich.edu/courses/eecs380/HANDOUTS/cppBinaryFileIO-2.html https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2225600/whats-the-difference-between-opening-a-file-with-iosbinary-or-iosout-or-bot 9. Do rvalue references to const have any use?参考 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4938875/do-rvalue-references-to-const-have-any-use 10. Slice Problem12345678910111213141516171819202122232425262728293031323334353637383940414243444546474849505152#include &lt;iostream&gt;using namespace std;// Base classclass A &#123; public: A() &#123;&#125; A(const A&amp; a) &#123; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;&#x27;A&#x27; copy constructor&quot; &lt;&lt; endl; &#125; virtual void run() const &#123; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;I am an &#x27;A&#x27;&quot; &lt;&lt; endl; &#125;&#125;;// Derived classclass B : public A &#123; public: B() : A() &#123;&#125; B(const B&amp; a) : A(a) &#123; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;&#x27;B&#x27; copy constructor&quot; &lt;&lt; endl; &#125; virtual void run() const &#123; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;I am a &#x27;B&#x27;&quot; &lt;&lt; endl; &#125;&#125;;void g(const A&amp; a) &#123; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;vptr2: &quot; &lt;&lt; hex &lt;&lt; *reinterpret_cast&lt;unsigned long*&gt;(const_cast&lt;A*&gt;(&amp;a)) &lt;&lt; endl; a.run();&#125;void h(const A a) &#123; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;vptr1: &quot; &lt;&lt; hex &lt;&lt; *reinterpret_cast&lt;unsigned long*&gt;(const_cast&lt;A*&gt;(&amp;a)) &lt;&lt; endl; a.run();&#125;int main() &#123; B a; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;vptr: &quot; &lt;&lt; hex &lt;&lt; *reinterpret_cast&lt;unsigned long*&gt;(&amp;a) &lt;&lt; endl; cout &lt;&lt; &quot;Call by reference&quot; &lt;&lt; endl; g(a); cout &lt;&lt; endl &lt;&lt; &quot;Call by copy&quot; &lt;&lt; endl; h(a);&#125;// Possible Output:// vptr: 10c4ed050// Call by reference// vptr2: 10c4ed050// I am a &#x27;B&#x27;// Call by copy// &#x27;A&#x27; copy constructor// vptr1: 10c4ed090// I am an &#x27;A&#x27; 参考 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/274626/what-is-object-slicing#274636 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/274626/what-is-object-slicing C++ Syntax1234567891011121314151617181920//=== [expr.post.general] ===//postfix-expression: primary-expression postfix-expression [ expression-list&lt;opt&gt; ] postfix-expression ( expression-list&lt;opt&gt; ) simple-type-specifier ( expression-list&lt;opt&gt; ) typename-specifier ( expression-list&lt;opt&gt; simple-type-specifier braced-init-list typename-specifier braced-init-list postfix-expression . template&lt;opt&gt;id-expression postfix-expression -&gt; template&lt;opt&gt;id-expression postfix-expression ++ postfix-expression -- dynamic_cast &lt; type-id &gt; ( expression ) static_cast &lt; type-id &gt; ( expression ) reinterpret_cast &lt; type-id &gt; ( expression ) const_cast &lt; type-id &gt; ( expression ) typeid ( expression ) typeid ( type-id ) 123456789101112131415161718192021222324252627282930313233343536//=== [dcl.dcl] ===//initializer: brace-or-equal-initializer ( expression-list ) brace-or-equal-initializer: = initializer-clause braced-init-list initializer-clause: assignment-expression braced-init-listbraced-init-list: &#123; initializer-list ,opt &#125; &#123; designated-initializer-list , opt &#125; &#123; &#125;initializer-list: initializer-clause ...opt initializer-list, initializer-clause ...opt designated-initializer-list: designated-initializer-clause designated-initializer-list , designated-initializer-clause designated-initializer-clause: designator brace-or-equal-initializerdesignator: .identifierexpr-or-braced-init-list: expression braced-init-list Pointers to Member Functionshttps://isocpp.org/wiki/faq/pointers-to-members what is std::identity and how it is used?参考 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15202474/default-function-that-just-returns-the-passed-value https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41767240/what-is-stdidentity-and-how-it-is-used Why do byte spills occur and what do they achieve?参考 https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16453314/why-do-byte-spills-occur-and-what-do-they-achieve C++四种cast参考https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/151744661 Back to Basics: const and constexpr const const_cast Modifying a const declared object by removing its constness is undefine behavior Don’t use a C-cast (int i = (int) myValue;), because it applies eventually a series of casts: static_cast =&gt; const_cast =&gt; reinterpret_cast 12345678910111213#include &lt;iostream&gt;using namespace std;int main() &#123; const int constInt = 10; const int* pToConstInt = &amp;constInt; int* pToInt = const_cast&lt;int*&gt;(pToConstInt); *pToInt = 12; // undefined behavior cout &lt;&lt; constInt &lt;&lt